  "publisher": "the_boys",
  "about": "William J. Butcher is a fictional character and one of the two main protagonists of the comic book series The Boys, created by Garth Ennis and Darick Robertson. He is the leader of The Boys, a group of CIA-sponsored black ops agents who observe, record and sometimes eliminate superheroes artificially created by the mega-conglomerate Vought. He is the Homelander's archenemy, whom he blames for the rape and death of his wife Becky, while also developing an obsessive, intense hatred for all superhuman beings, which transforms him throughout the series from an anti-heroic figure into a villainous one. Butcher also appears as one of the two protagonists, alongside Hughie, in the Amazon Prime Video television adaptation of The Boys.",
